balloons.comments: BLT-67 was launched on the morning of Tuesday (02 Feb 2021) from NW Houston.  It is the maiden flight of my new picoballoon tracker, the SS_PicoTrackerFW (FW = Feather Weight), coming in around 1.4g board weight, and total payload weight of 7.28g.  The solar cells comprise most of that weight, but I'm working on that for the next launch.

Testing with the intention of using a Lithium super capacitor Decoding TELEN The second Telen number leads with a 0 or a 1 if it is a 0 then the First 4 digits on the first number is battery voltage in millivolts the next two numbers represent the last two digits of the outside temperature in kelvin on the second number the last 5 numbers is altitude in meters if the second telen number leads with a 1 the first 3 numbers of the first number is the outside temperature in kelvin the next two numbers are cloud reflection and the last number is a 0 for low power tx and a 1 for high power tx The second number decodes with the second third and forth digit representing the number of transmission since initial programming ( up to 999) and the last two digits are the transmissions since sunrise this day .Using an 80 farad supercap that is charged by a 4 volt ldo regulator to keep it within voltage range
